pull_request.title: Use OpenSSL error schemes
pull_request.body:
The OpenSSL error handling works as follows:

* Per module (e.g. `crypto/ec`) a namespace is made (`ECerr`)
* In that namespace, all `ECerr` calls are scraped
* The location parameter should be `EC_F_<functionname>`
* The reason should be `ERR_R_reason`.
* Then you run `make errors`: this scrapes the above out of the places
where they are used and puts them into the appropriate headerfiles.

I've turned `OQSerr` back into `ECerr`, because otherwise `make errors`
was broken. I've also added some reasons other than `ERR_R_FATAL`.
